Baska bir yere gittim ve aslinda 10 $ daha ucuza satin aldim, muhtemelen tekrar geri donmeyecek.
featured_reviews.response_from_owner_translated_text: Geri bildiriminizi bizimle paylasmak uzere zaman ayirdiginiz icin tesekkur ederiz. Tum musteri etkilesimlerine gercekten deger veriyoruz ve magazamizdaki her etkilesimin olumlu olmasi icin calisiyoruz. Son ziyaretinizin musteri hizmetleriyle ilgili beklentilerinizi karsilamadigini duydugumuz icin uzgunuz. Amacimiz kaliteli hizmet sunmaktir ve personelimizle etkilesiminiz sirasinda meydana gelen herhangi bir yanlis iletisim veya yanlis anlama icin ozur dileriz. Argo kullanimina gelince, bunun kasitsiz olabilecegini anliyoruz ve musterilerimizi magaza politikalarimiz konusunda egitmenin daha iyi yollari uzerinde calisacagiz. Bu sohbete devam etmek istiyorsaniz, lutfen bize cs@temptationsgroup.com adresinden e-posta gonderin.

featured_reviews.review_id:
A valid Wisconsin Drivers License will not get you in here.
My fiance and I tried to visit tonight (we have visited before with no issues). She is 21, I am 23. AKA, well above the age allowed in to an establishment such as this. The girl came to check our IDs(did not get her name, but she was a blond girl who was working at around 9PM on Sunday August 6). My fiance's older, vertical drivers license checked out fine. However, when she checked my horizontal drivers license (one of the new black and white ones), she looked at it for a long time. I then told her "It's one of the new ones". She said she knew it was, but that it looked "different". When I asked her to elaborate on how exactly it looked "different", she would not give me any reason. After looking at it for awhile, she told me she "didn't feel comfortable letting me in with this".
Not one to argue with a business that does not want my money, I politely left. I was absolutely in shock, I have never had a person reject my actual drivers license before.
So if you're planning on going here, you better bring a long form birth certificate, a United States Passport, your social security card and a note from your mother because apparently a drivers license just won't do.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Gecerli bir Wisconsin Surucu Belgesi sizi buraya sokmayacaktir.
Nisanlim ve ben bu gece ziyaret etmeye calistik (daha once hicbir sorun yasamadan ziyaret etmistik). O 21 yasinda, ben 23. Yani boyle bir kuruma girilmesine izin verilen yasin cok ustunde. Kiz kimliklerimizi kontrol etmeye geldi (adini alamadi ama 6 Agustos Pazar gunu saat 21.00 civarinda calisan sarisin bir kizdi). Nisanlimin eski, dikey ehliyetinin durumu iyi. Ancak yatay ehliyetimi (yeni siyah beyaz olanlardan biri) kontrol ettiginde uzun sure bakti. Daha sonra ona "Bu yenilerden biri" dedim. Oyle oldugunu bildigini ancak "farkli" gorundugunu soyledi. Ondan tam olarak nasil "farkli" gorundugunu aciklamasini istedigimde bana herhangi bir sebep vermedi. Bir sure baktiktan sonra bana "bununla ilgilenmeme izin verme konusunda kendini rahat hissetmedigini" soyledi.
Parami istemeyen bir isletmeyle tartisacak biri degilim, kibarca ayrildim. Kesinlikle soktaydim, daha once hic kimsenin gercek ehliyetimi reddetmesini gormemistim.
Yani buraya gitmeyi planliyorsaniz, uzun sureli bir dogum belgesi, Amerika Birlesik Devletleri Pasaportu, sosyal guvenlik kartiniz ve annenizden bir not getirseniz iyi olur cunku gorunuse gore ehliyet ise yaramayacak.

Not touching anything. Then a lady on the phone in back YELLS at me for leaning around to look at price. And with an attitude says that if I want to look at something, someone has to grab it for me.
Well thank you for your unwanted attitude, so due to that I will never return and give my money to employees who want to embarrass customers due to eyesight issues with their small price tags.

Solution: instead of yelling at customers and giving an attitude because you hate your job. Just ask if you can help with something. It would make your day go by quickly and result in increased sales.

ZAMAN VEYA PARA KAYBETMEYIN. KABA CALISANLAR. Bir sure kimsenin yardimi olmadan raftaki cam fiyatlarina bakiyordum. Fiyat etiketleri o kadar kucuk ki, sirf fiyata bakmak icin tezgahin arkasina dogru egildim. Hicbir seye dokunmamak. Sonra arkadaki telefondaki bir bayan, fiyata bakmak icin egildigim icin bana bagiriyor. Ve bir tavirla, eger bir seye bakmak istersem birinin onu benim icin yakalamasi gerektigini soyluyor.
Istenmeyen tavriniz icin tesekkur ederim, bu nedenle asla geri donmeyecegim ve parami, kucuk fiyat etiketleri ile gorme sorunlari nedeniyle musterileri utandirmak isteyen calisanlara vermeyecegim.

Cozum: Musterilere bagirmak ve isinizden nefret ettiginiz icin tavir almak yerine. Bir konuda yardim edip edemeyeceginizi sorun. Gununuzun hizli gecmesini saglar ve satislarin artmasina neden olur.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I've come here twice now, and have a couple of toys. It's expensive, but I think well worth the money. Quality is awesome and haven't had any complaints.
Staff is also friendly and nothing really fazes them (which is perfect for first timers or more timid buyers). They answer questions you may have, and the first time I came, they also had instructional videos for first time toy users.

featured_reviews.review_id:
I honestly was terrified of coming into this store and I debated on it for three days  I finally found the courage and not only was I welcomed in, the employees answered my nonstop questions and walked me through the whole store and all of their products! Yes there were other customers in there, but the environment was SO comfortable! The way the store is staged, you feel a sense of comfort and security in how you shop! They also have fencing on the windows so that you do have privacy - and brown bags upon purchase for privacy too! They have so many cute shirts and cards and games to play - let me tell you - I'll be back! 
If you're a beginner, fear not! It was such a fun trip and I learned so much!

featured_reviews.review_id: Cute lil inclusive shop! It's great to come here with my partner, but also with friends just to look around and have fun. Amazing selection considering it's a smaller shop. Every staff member I've met is friendly funny n welcoming :) The storefront is really cute (they commit to the tool shed theme) but the windows are still blocked out for discretion. Toys will always come in a plain paper bag too! Employees are also good about masking. I usually bring mine but forgot it last night, and the employees still let me shop so that was nice.

featured_reviews.review_id:
As a first time shopper at an "adult" establishment my expectation was that I would be walking into a dingy room with a seedy vibe. This was not the case at all. The Tool Shed resembles a suburban boutique with descriptive tags on all their items, respectful staff, and a LGBT positive selection of items.

Additionally, when I returned home and realized that the batteries in my new purchase had corroded with age I was offered a replacement should the device itself been affected.

Will definitely visit again in the future!
